\section{Preliminaries on central simple algebras}

In this section, we extend the methods pioneered in \cite{poonenUniversalExistential} from quaternion algebras over ${\mathbb{Q}}$ to general central simple algebras of prime degree over number fields. Apart from our local-global principle, whose proof follows the idea set out in Theorem 3.1 of \cite{eisentraegerIntegralityAtAPrime}, all proofs are essentially the same as in Poonen's paper.

